---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";
import Contact from "../components/Contact.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Pricing — SymFynity"
  description="SymFynity, the source-available circuit breaker, is free to run forever under BSL 1.1. SymFynity Cloud is priced by conversation while we onboard early customers by hand."
>
  <Section as="h1" lead label="Pricing" heading="SymFynity is free forever. The platform starts with a conversation.">
    <div class="prose stack">
      <p>
        Self-hosting SymFynity costs nothing and always will. It isn't crippled without us,
        and there's no tier of it that we hold back. If that's all you ever need, take
        it — that's the point of shipping it that way.
      </p>
      <p>
        SymFynity is source-available under BSL 1.1, which isn't the same as open source and
        we won't pretend otherwise. In practice the difference reaches you only if you
        try to resell SymFynity as a hosted service competing with us. Running it in
        production, on your own infrastructure, for your own traffic, is explicitly free
        — and four years after each release, that version turns Apache-2.0 on its own.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section label="The two options" heading="What you get, and what it costs.">
    <div class="cols">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="tag oss">BSL 1.1</span>
        <h3>SymFynity, self-hosted</h3>
        <p class="price">Free</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Rolling token budgets per tenant</li>
          <li>Inline enforcement on streaming and non-streaming</li>
          <li>Model and tool policy blocking</li>
          <li>Local event log via <code>/events</code></li>
          <li>Hot-reloading config, no restart</li>
          <li>Runs entirely in your infrastructure</li>
          <li>Becomes Apache-2.0 four years after release</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/SymFynity/symfynity" rel="noopener">
          Get SymFynity
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <span class="tag">Commercial</span>
        <h3>SymFynity Cloud</h3>
        <p class="price">Let's talk</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Everything in SymFynity, unchanged</li>
          <li>Fleet-wide spend visibility across instances</li>
          <li>Alerting before budgets trip</li>
          <li>Compliance reporting on blocked models and tools</li>
          <li>Historical usage across every tenant</li>
        </ul>
        <Contact />
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section label="Why there's no pricing table" heading="Because we'd be making it up.">
    <div class="prose stack">
      <p>
        We're onboarding early customers by hand — deliberately. Every account is
        activated manually, which means we talk to you before you can send us a single
        event. That's a real constraint in the product, not a growth tactic.
      </p>
      <p>
        Publishing tiers now would mean inventing numbers before we understand what the
        platform is worth to the people using it. You'd anchor on them, we'd regret them,
        and one of us would be wrong. Ask us instead — and if SymFynity on its own covers you,
        we'll say so.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>
</Base>

<style>
  .stack {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .cols {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 48rem) {
    .cols {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 2.5rem;
    }
  }

  .card {
    border-top: 2px solid var(--brass);
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .card h3 {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .price {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--brass);
  }

  .card ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    font-size: 0.96875rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .card ul li::marker {
    color: var(--brass);
  }

  .tag {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-label);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.45rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    color: var(--ink-muted);
  }

  .tag.oss {
    color: var(--flow);
    border-color: var(--flow);
  }
</style>
